In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 21 to October 27, 2012, as National Character Counts Week. The article emphasizes the importance of personal integrity, mutual respect, and commitment to service as guiding principles for the progress of the nation. It highlights the responsibility of parents, teachers, mentors, and neighbors to empower children with excellence in all aspects of life and instill values of responsibility and service. The article also addresses the issue of bullying and harassment, urging the creation of safe spaces that nurture empathy and regard for others. The proclamation concludes with a call for the preservation and passing on of American values.